  - computational-social-science
  - temperature-anomaly
  - reanalysis
  - ERA5
  - 20CRv3
  - HadCET
abstract: >-
  ThermoStrife is the human-data companion to the ThermoKourt
  Drosophila pipeline. It curates 112 violent uprisings,
  revolutions, massacres, and prison revolts from 1750 to 2024
  with day-of-event maximum air temperature resolved through a
  four-tier weather-archive cascade (meteostat GHCN / ECA&D /
  DWD stations, HadCET, ECMWF ERA5 reanalysis, NOAA 20CRv3
  reanalysis), each event paired with a station-and-month-matched
  five-year decadal baseline drawn from the same underlying
  series. The pre-registered case-crossover conditional-logit
  analysis tests whether positive temperature anomalies are
  over-represented on uprising days against a null built from
  matched non-event days at the same station; v0.1.0 reports a
  headline odds ratio of 1.089 per +1 degC above local same-month
  baseline (95 percent CI 1.029 to 1.152, one-sided p = 0.0016)
  on 104 of 112 resolved events, with a 41-event peaceful-crowd
  parallel control showing the opposite direction (OR 0.961,
  p = 0.83) as a Field-1992 outdoor-opportunity falsification.
